Step 1 — Transcript Analysis Prompt

Use this first.

Act as a senior federal program manager and enterprise architect.

Analyze the meeting transcript and convert it into structured program management outputs.

Focus on extracting operational commitments, governance decisions, risks, and dependencies.

Organize the output using the following sections.

⸻

EXECUTIVE SUMMARY
Provide a concise overview of the meeting purpose and outcomes.

⸻

KEY DECISIONS
List decisions made during the meeting.

Include:
Decision
Decision Owner
Rationale
Impact

⸻

ACTION ITEMS
Create a table with the following columns:

Action Item
Owner
Priority
Deadline
Dependencies

⸻

RISKS AND BLOCKERS

For each risk include:
Risk description
Impact
Likelihood
Mitigation strategy

⸻

OPEN QUESTIONS

List unresolved questions requiring follow-up.

⸻

KEY FACTS AND INFORMATION

Extract important facts including:
technologies
systems
policy references
metrics
timelines

⸻

STAKEHOLDERS

List teams, agencies, or individuals referenced.

⸻

MEETING NOTES

Provide a clean set of readable meeting notes.

